A cold wallet is a wallet kept offline (no internet connection).
It is used to store large funds securely.

âœ… Very secure (cannot be hacked remotely)
âŒ Slow access (manual approval, extra steps)

Use case: Long-term storage / treasury funds.

ğŸ”¥ Hot Wallet

A hot wallet is a wallet connected to the internet.
Used for daily transactions (withdrawals, swaps, payments).

âœ… Fast and automated
âŒ More exposed to hacking risk

